 deficits and explain how the formal mechanisms of democratic statehood need to be complemented and updated in new ways today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCritical theory. 0aSociology. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Critical Theory.2bisacsh  aFrankfurt School.  aKeynesianism.  acritical theory.  afunctional differentiation.  ahistorical bloc.  alifeworld.  apassive revolution.  asocial systems.  asystems theory.  awar of position.1 aSchecter, Darrow, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2019 eBook-Packagez978311128249740uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614226940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526142269423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526142269/original  a978-3-11-128249-7  Manchester University Press 2019 eBook-Packageb2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles